---
// The Billionaires at the White House Table
import { Rocket, Eye, Building2, DollarSign, LandPlot, FileText, TrendingUp } from 'lucide-astro';
---

<section class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-navy text-white">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-12">
    <div class="section-line bg-red-500 mb-6"></div>
    <h2 class="font-display font-extrabold text-3xl md:text-4xl tracking-tight mb-3">
      The Billionaires at the White House Table
    </h2>
    <p class="font-body text-xl text-gray-300 max-w-3xl mb-10">
      While you fill out your tax forms, tech billionaires are dining with the President and walking away with billions in government contracts. Same companies. Same donors. Same results.
    </p>

    <!-- Musk -->
    <div class="card-dark p-6 mb-6">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-4">
        <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-red-500/20 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
          <Rocket class="w-7 h-7 text-red-400" />
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-white">Elon Musk / Tesla + SpaceX</h3>
          <div class="font-mono text-sm text-gray-400">$277M+ donated to Trump 2024 campaign</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-4">
        <div>
          <div class="font-mono text-xs text-red-400 mb-2">TOTAL GOVERNMENT SUPPORT</div>
          <div class="stat-large text-white">$38B+</div>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-2">
            In contracts, loans, subsidies, and tax credits since 2003
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="font-mono text-xs text-red-400 mb-2">2024 ALONE</div>
          <div class="stat-large text-white">$6.3B</div>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-2">
            Highest single-year government support in company history
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-3 mb-4">
        <div class="bg-white/5 p-3 rounded-xl">
          <div class="text-white font-semibold">SpaceX NASA</div>
          <div class="font-mono text-xl text-red-400">$15B+</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-gray-400">Including Moon program</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white/5 p-3 rounded-xl">
          <div class="text-white font-semibold">Tesla Subsidies</div>
          <div class="font-mono text-xl text-red-400">$11.4B</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-gray-400">Regulatory credits alone</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white/5 p-3 rounded-xl">
          <div class="text-white font-semibold">2010 DOE Loan</div>
          <div class="font-mono text-xl text-red-400">$465M</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-gray-400">"Tesla wouldn't have survived"</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <p class="font-body text-gray-400 text-sm">
        <strong class="text-white">The twist:</strong> Musk led "DOGE" to cut government spending — while his companies remain among the largest government contractors. He now supports ending EV subsidies, which he says "would be devastating for our competitors."
      </p>
      <div class="font-mono text-xs text-gray-500 mt-3">Washington Post analysis, Feb 2025</div>
    </div>

    <!-- Thiel / Palantir -->
    <div class="card-dark p-6 mb-6">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-4">
        <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-blue-500/20 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
          <Eye class="w-7 h-7 text-blue-400" />
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-white">Peter Thiel / Palantir</h3>
          <div class="font-mono text-sm text-gray-400">PayPal co-founder with Musk, backed JD Vance's Senate campaign</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-4">
        <div>
          <div class="font-mono text-xs text-red-400 mb-2">2025 FEDERAL CONTRACTS</div>
          <div class="stat-large text-white">$970M</div>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-2">
            Nearly double the previous year ($541M in 2024)
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="font-mono text-xs text-red-400 mb-2">STOCK SURGE SINCE TRUMP WON</div>
          <div class="stat-large text-white">200%+</div>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-2">
            Market cap now over $400 billion
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-3 mb-4">
        <div class="bg-white/5 p-3 rounded-xl">
          <div class="text-white font-semibold">ICE Contract</div>
          <div class="font-mono text-xl text-red-400">$30M</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-gray-400">"ImmigrationOS" tracking</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white/5 p-3 rounded-xl">
          <div class="text-white font-semibold">Navy Contract</div>
          <div class="font-mono text-xl text-red-400">$1B</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-gray-400">Software platform</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white/5 p-3 rounded-xl">
          <div class="text-white font-semibold">DOD Contract</div>
          <div class="font-mono text-xl text-red-400">$795M</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-gray-400">Pentagon systems</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <p class="font-body text-gray-400 text-sm">
        <strong class="text-white">The strategy:</strong> "Thiel's played it very smart. He's basically not in the public eye like he was in 2022. He's just basically working the backroom deals." Company originally funded by CIA's In-Q-Tel venture arm.
      </p>
      <div class="font-mono text-xs text-gray-500 mt-3">The Hill / NPR / USAspending.gov, 2025</div>
    </div>

    <!-- Ellison / Oracle -->
    <div class="card-dark p-6 mb-6">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-4">
        <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-orange-500/20 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
          <Building2 class="w-7 h-7 text-orange-400" />
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-white">Larry Ellison / Oracle</h3>
          <div class="font-mono text-sm text-gray-400">Dines with Trump at Mar-a-Lago, bought $450M in real estate 20 min away</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-4">
        <div>
          <div class="font-mono text-xs text-red-400 mb-2">"STARGATE" AI PARTNERSHIP</div>
          <div class="stat-large text-white">$500B</div>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-2">
            Announced day after inauguration at White House with Trump
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="font-mono text-xs text-red-400 mb-2">ORACLE LOBBYING (2024)</div>
          <div class="stat-large text-white">$10M+</div>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-2">
            64 lobbyists including 4 former members of Congress
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-4">
        <div class="bg-white/5 p-3 rounded-xl">
          <div class="text-white font-semibold">TikTok Deal</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-400">Trump: "I'd like Larry to buy" TikTok. Oracle now leading investor group.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white/5 p-3 rounded-xl">
          <div class="text-white font-semibold">Paramount Takeover</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-400">Son David now CEO. CBS settled $16M lawsuit with Trump. Colbert cancelled.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <p class="font-body text-gray-400 text-sm">
        <strong class="text-white">The access:</strong> Oracle worked with Heritage Foundation to build database of Trump loyalists for Project 2025. Ellison proposed putting "all national data" into a single AI-fed database.
      </p>
      <div class="font-mono text-xs text-gray-500 mt-3">OpenSecrets / SF Chronicle / Slate, 2024-2025</div>
    </div>

    <!-- The Pattern -->
    <div class="card-dark p-6">
      <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-white text-center mb-6">
        The Pattern: Money → Access → Contracts → More Money
      </h3>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 mb-6">
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-red-500/20 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-2">
            <DollarSign class="w-6 h-6 text-red-400" />
          </div>
          <div class="font-semibold text-white text-sm">Donate</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-gray-400">$277M+ from Musk alone</div>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-red-500/20 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-2">
            <LandPlot class="w-6 h-6 text-red-400" />
          </div>
          <div class="font-semibold text-white text-sm">Access</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-gray-400">Mar-a-Lago dinners, WH events</div>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-red-500/20 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-2">
            <FileText class="w-6 h-6 text-red-400" />
          </div>
          <div class="font-semibold text-white text-sm">Contracts</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-gray-400">Billions in government deals</div>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-red-500/20 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-2">
            <TrendingUp class="w-6 h-6 text-red-400" />
          </div>
          <div class="font-semibold text-white text-sm">Stock Soars</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-gray-400">Palantir up 200%+</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="text-center pt-4 border-t border-white/10">
        <p class="font-body text-lg text-gray-300">
          Meanwhile, your business competes for contracts against companies whose founders sit at the President's table. <strong class="text-white">This isn't capitalism. It's cronyism.</strong>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
